Title: Why Write?
Description:
As a reaction to the previous article
on how to write a scientific paper, I got some reactions from friends
and colleagues, the underlying message being that they would rather like
to understand why writing can be important. There is indeed a tendency
to see academic writing as a tedious task that one should try to get
done as quickly as possible lest it causes unbearable pain,1 or,
even worse, that writing in general is a talent that you have to be
born with.

Title: Spark is still a safe port when compared to DuckDB and Polars
Description: The author faced obstacles and encountered performance issues with DuckDB and Polars, while Spark proved to be a reliable and efficient solution. The experience highlights the importance of having the necessary skills to work with these technologies and implies that Spark just works when it comes to data processing tasks.
